<br>
My proposal? Standardize, more or less, items and zones. Upgrade 'old world', perhaps Kunark and Velious items from quests and drops that used to be sought after so that they are once again used, on par with some of the more recent items of their difficulty to obtain from LoY, LDoN, Luclin, and PoP. Furthermore, revamp old world dungeons and convert some of them into LDoN style dungeon groupings. Good candidates would be Cazic-Thule, Crushbone, Castle Mistmoore, Kaesora, and so on. Align these new LDoN-style dungeons with given factions (for example, Crushbone with Kelethin and Kaladim, Kaesora with the Overthere, Firiona Vie, and Cabilis, and so on). Allow one to obtain items from these areas for old world quests still through adventuring. And so forth. I imagine this would make visiting some of these old zones and doing old quests worthwhile again.<br>
<br>
While the LDoN style conversion is optional, I DO think that the upgrading of old items and quests to meet the current par is necessary. It would no longer make old items obsolete.<br>
<br>
What do you think? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=buvin>Buvin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>the ever dying ranger<br>Bad Bow Boy</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/31/03 11:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4779.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: An idea; whatcha think?</span><hr size=1> But then why would people pay Sony for the expansions? <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~mcjohnson/images/EQ/sig55.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
